WEBVTT

00:28.802 --> 00:30.364
Hello, welcome to God Day.

00:31.005 --> 00:33.307
I'm Derek Walker, the pastor of the Oxford Bible Church.

00:33.888 --> 00:52.851
Today we're talking about the prodigal father, or really Luke chapter 15, in which we see a trinity of parables, but we're the main one being, what's normally known as the parable of the prodigal son, but it's really about the prodigal father.

00:53.592 --> 00:58.738
Anyway, there are three stories in Luke 15 that all reveal

00:59.266 --> 01:03.091
and are parables that reveal the love of God for us.

01:03.171 --> 01:04.814
God's extravagant love actually.

01:05.374 --> 01:08.539
And they are just like the Trinity, Father, Son and Holy Spirit.

01:08.599 --> 01:20.775
So one parable is about the Father, another about the Son and another about the Holy Spirit, and they all have this abundant love for us that is revealed in the parable.

01:20.796 --> 01:24.120
And it's a triune chapter in other words.

01:24.180 --> 01:28.466
And you've always got the case of something that is lost that is

01:29.122 --> 01:35.972
a picture of us, and when we are found, then there is great rejoicing in heaven.

01:36.392 --> 01:38.255
That's how much God loves us.

01:39.497 --> 01:47.107
It isn't a case that if we go astray and we come back, that God is kind of saying, oh, he's back, is he?

01:47.408 --> 01:47.708
Fine.

01:48.710 --> 01:50.672
No, God is excited.

01:50.692 --> 01:55.940
That's how much he loves us, how important it is that we are back with him.

01:56.861 --> 01:57.522
Anyway,

01:57.634 --> 02:07.150
It's interesting in Matthew 15, verse three, it says, let's start in verse one.

02:07.550 --> 02:10.656
Then all the tax collectors and sinners drew near to him to hear him.

02:11.217 --> 02:16.265
And the Pharisees inscribed, complain saying, this man received sinners and eats with them.

02:16.866 --> 02:21.714
So they can't understand why Jesus would mix with sinners.

02:22.146 --> 02:25.649
You know, and then he spoke this parable to them.

02:25.709 --> 02:28.432
Notice just the one parable, but it's in three parts.

02:29.133 --> 02:32.276
And this parable reveals that God loves sinners.

02:32.296 --> 02:35.218
And if only the Pharisees would know it, they were sinners too.

02:36.500 --> 02:39.102
But anyway, this is the love of God for all of us.

02:39.623 --> 02:51.794
The first parable speaks of the love of God the Son, who is the good shepherd, who discovers, seeks and finds the lost sheep.

02:52.322 --> 02:54.844
The second one is a picture of God the Holy Spirit.

02:55.325 --> 02:59.409
It's pictured by a woman who seeks and finds a lost coin.

02:59.989 --> 03:06.956
And the third speaks of the love of God the Father for his lost son, often known as the prodigal son.

03:08.297 --> 03:20.408
And so how valuable something is to us is revealed by how much time and effort we spend to find it if it's lost and our joy on recovering it.

03:20.528 --> 03:22.290
So these parables reveal

03:22.626 --> 03:31.258
how important we are to God and how much God rejoices when he finds us again.

03:31.298 --> 03:32.259
Hallelujah.

03:32.560 --> 03:36.705
So let's look at the first one, which is the parable of the shepherd and the lost sheep.

03:37.446 --> 03:41.372
And this is a picture of the work of the sun in salvation.

03:43.134 --> 03:48.722
What man of you, he says, now this is in verse four, what man of you

03:49.090 --> 03:56.878
Having a hundred sheep, if he loses one of them, doesn't leave the 99 in the wilderness and go after the one which was lost until he finds it.

03:57.238 --> 04:00.241
And when he's found it, he lays it on his shoulders rejoicing.

04:00.902 --> 04:07.648
And when he comes home, he calls together his friends and neighbors saying to them, Rejoice with me, for I've found my sheep which was lost.

04:08.049 --> 04:17.298
I say to you that likewise there'll be more joy in heaven over one sinner who repents than over 99 just persons who need no repentance.

04:17.570 --> 04:19.493
So here's the shepherd with a hundred sheep.

04:20.414 --> 04:23.399
And as sheep do, it went astray.

04:23.720 --> 04:24.381
It got lost.

04:25.282 --> 04:27.606
This sheep was stupid.

04:27.626 --> 04:31.812
It thought it could look after itself because sheep can't manage by themselves.

04:32.173 --> 04:33.154
They need their shepherd.

04:33.775 --> 04:37.080
And so he went his own way, got lost in the wilderness.

04:37.681 --> 04:39.444
And this is a very dangerous place.

04:40.125 --> 04:44.131
All kinds of pits he could fall into, wolves who would eat him and so on.

04:44.352 --> 04:45.874
He would die for sure.

04:46.338 --> 04:47.379
if he was on his own.

04:48.020 --> 04:50.744
And the sheep is helpless to protect itself.

04:51.525 --> 04:54.029
And he doesn't know now how to get home again.

04:54.109 --> 04:54.610
He's lost.

04:55.451 --> 04:58.134
And the Bible says that all we like sheep have gone astray.

04:58.455 --> 05:01.399
We've turned everyone to his own way, Isaiah 53, 6.

05:01.980 --> 05:03.442
And so we go astray.

05:03.482 --> 05:05.144
We say, oh, I'm fine.

05:05.485 --> 05:07.367
I don't need God in my life.

05:07.447 --> 05:13.676
I'll look after myself and how foolish we are when we think that way.

05:14.597 --> 05:15.058
And

05:15.394 --> 05:17.217
Eventually we realize we're lost.

05:17.677 --> 05:18.258
We're alone.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.000
We don't know the way home.

05:20.862 --> 05:24.447
And Jesus said in John 10, he says, I am the good shepherd.

05:24.467 --> 05:26.570
The good shepherd gives his life for the sheep.

05:27.211 --> 05:29.193
I lay down my life for the sheep, he says.

05:30.836 --> 05:42.552
And Matthew 936, it says, when he saw the multitudes, he was moved with compassion for them because they were weary and scattered like sheep having no shepherd.

05:43.173 --> 05:43.954
And so,

05:44.098 --> 05:49.386
It would have been easy for this shepherd to say, look, I've lost one, but I've still got 99 sheep.

05:50.207 --> 05:51.449
Serves him right anyway.

05:51.950 --> 05:53.553
He went off by himself.

05:54.254 --> 05:57.739
And sometimes people think God is like that.

05:57.839 --> 05:59.522
He doesn't particularly care for me.

06:00.263 --> 06:04.189
But actually, God is like this, that he left the 99.

06:04.209 --> 06:09.417
And he had, in other words, he had a personal love for this one sheep that was lost.

06:10.699 --> 06:12.722
Yes, Jesus died for the whole world.

06:12.802 --> 06:17.107
But if you were the only one who needed saving, he would have come and died for you.

06:17.167 --> 06:18.528
This is what this parable says.

06:19.029 --> 06:28.819
That even if there was just one lost, he would leave where he is and seek to save that lost sheep.

06:29.280 --> 06:37.128
And so here's this shepherd going out in the evening, in the night, calling out to this sheep.

06:38.089 --> 06:39.251
He refused to give up.

06:39.351 --> 06:42.354
He went through dangerous places, calling out

06:42.914 --> 07:03.506
where the world beasts would move and he was calling out where are you calling his name and Jesus said in Luke 19 10 I've come to seek and save the lost and at some point maybe after few hours even he heard a pathetic bleeding the sheep was weak and injured he couldn't move

07:03.586 --> 07:05.448
And it was helpless to save itself.

07:05.528 --> 07:08.391
It's probably trapped in some thorn bush or something like that.

07:09.012 --> 07:10.133
All it could do is bleed.

07:11.295 --> 07:18.442
And the shepherd heard the sound and followed the sound and found it perhaps in a dangerous pit.

07:19.183 --> 07:23.748
And so I imagine him just climbing down into that pit.

07:24.269 --> 07:26.531
It was getting dark and he took hold of the sheep.

07:26.591 --> 07:32.498
And it says, when he had found it, he laid it on his shoulders and carried it home rejoicing.

07:32.962 --> 07:33.943
He was so happy.

07:34.043 --> 07:35.484
This is a picture of salvation.

07:35.825 --> 07:37.166
See, we can't save ourselves.

07:37.186 --> 07:37.666
We're lost.

07:38.047 --> 07:39.949
But Jesus, our good shepherd, came to us.

07:40.669 --> 07:43.492
And all he needed is for us to bleed.

07:43.972 --> 07:48.937
We just had to go, Jesus, we call on the name of the Lord Jesus.

07:49.017 --> 07:49.638
Save me.

07:50.619 --> 07:55.343
And so this sheep heard the voice of the shepherd reaching out to him.

07:55.804 --> 07:57.685
And he called out like we do.

07:58.326 --> 07:59.968
Lord, we call on the name of the Lord.

08:00.008 --> 08:02.450
And all who call on the name of the Lord shall be saved.

08:02.594 --> 08:05.617
And Jesus came comes and he reaches down.

08:06.177 --> 08:11.262
He as it were went into the pit of hell for us and on the cross to save us.

08:12.063 --> 08:17.388
And now he carries us back home into the kingdom of God, Hallelujah.

08:17.788 --> 08:19.110
And it's all by grace.

08:19.810 --> 08:23.654
And so this good shepherd climbed out of the pit full of joy.

08:24.275 --> 08:25.636
He wasn't angry with the sheep.

08:25.656 --> 08:26.497
He was just happy.

08:26.537 --> 08:27.878
They were reunited again.

08:28.579 --> 08:32.082
And so this is a wonderful picture of salvation.

08:32.994 --> 08:36.178
And Jesus is our good shepherd.

08:36.218 --> 08:43.308
Hebrews 1310, 20 says, God brought again from the dead, our Lord Jesus, that great shepherd of the sheep.

08:44.149 --> 08:54.483
And 1 Peter 2, 25 says, we were all a sheep going astray, but we have now returned to the shepherd and guardian of our soul.

08:55.044 --> 08:56.586
Have you returned to your shepherd?

08:57.427 --> 08:59.730
And then when the sheep was found,

09:00.130 --> 09:06.341
He wasn't just restored and reunited to the shepherd, but also to the 99 other sheep.

09:06.882 --> 09:09.326
He joined the fellowship of the flock.

09:09.346 --> 09:10.248
He joined the church.

09:11.209 --> 09:13.994
And so this is a picture of salvation.

09:14.375 --> 09:22.168
And then he wasn't satisfied with that because he had a party to celebrate the fact that the shepherd was now saved.

09:22.288 --> 09:25.554
And so it says, verse six, when he comes home,

09:25.730 --> 09:31.759
He calls together his friends and neighbors saying to them, Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep which was lost.

09:32.360 --> 09:40.272
And I say to you that likewise there will be more joy in heaven over one sinner who repents than over 99 just persons who need no repentance.

09:40.332 --> 09:43.236
And so he calls, he's so happy.

09:43.517 --> 09:44.699
He can't keep it to himself.

09:44.739 --> 09:45.740
He invites all his friends.

09:45.780 --> 09:54.834
He has a party and that's the way God celebrates in heaven when anyone gets born again, when anyone repents of going their own way.

09:55.106 --> 10:01.896
And let's Jesus carry them to safety in the kingdom of heaven, praise God.

10:02.297 --> 10:07.806
And so God loves each one of us individually, not just all corporately.

10:08.727 --> 10:12.533
And we are those sheep who are powerless to save themselves.

10:13.935 --> 10:17.480
So we can all say Psalm 23, the Lord is my shepherd.

10:18.282 --> 10:20.745
I shall not want hallelujah.

10:20.766 --> 10:21.106
Well,

10:21.218 --> 10:22.300
That's the first parable.

10:22.340 --> 10:29.450
That's pictures the love of Jesus, our shepherd, the son of God, our shepherd who came to seek and save the lost.

10:29.891 --> 10:30.512
Hallelujah.

10:31.013 --> 10:33.316
Well, the second parable is the lost coin.

10:33.857 --> 10:35.439
And that's in verse eight to 10.

10:35.920 --> 10:40.807
And this is pictures the Holy Spirit, the work of the Holy Spirit and our salvation.

10:41.549 --> 10:42.189
Let's read that.

10:42.510 --> 10:45.234
Or what woman having 10 silver coins?

10:45.538 --> 10:51.191
There's probably her dowry that she would keep a necklace of 10 silver coins.

10:52.233 --> 10:56.664
If she loses one coin, one coin falls off the necklace and it gets lost.

10:57.485 --> 10:58.127
What does she do?

10:58.969 --> 11:01.234
Does she not light a lamp?

11:01.378 --> 11:11.612
sweep the house and search carefully till she finds it and when she's found it she calls her neighbors and friends together saying rejoice with me for I found the peace which I lost.

11:11.692 --> 11:18.081
Likewise I say to you there is joy in the presence of the angels of God over just one sinner who repents.

11:18.261 --> 11:27.954
You see it's the same story told again slightly differently the woman this time and she represents the Holy Spirit.

11:28.450 --> 11:37.865
She had ten pieces of silver, drachma of silver, valuable coins that she would have worn around as a necklace probably.

11:38.566 --> 11:42.452
And she might think, well, I've still got nine out of ten, that's all right.

11:43.113 --> 11:49.322
No, she loved each of these coins, just like the Lord loves each one of us.

11:50.164 --> 11:51.666
And it fell, you see,

11:51.778 --> 11:53.861
on the dusty floor in the house.

11:53.881 --> 11:54.782
And the house is dark.

11:54.802 --> 11:57.005
They didn't have electrical lights in those days.

11:57.786 --> 12:01.692
And these coins are a picture of us.

12:01.752 --> 12:06.338
You see, we bear, there's an image on a coin and we are made in God's image.

12:06.438 --> 12:13.248
God, we belong to God, but we were lost in the darkness, in the dust of this world.

12:13.929 --> 12:20.498
And so she, instead of being in the Lord's presence,

12:20.674 --> 12:30.406
as it were, like this necklace around his neck, possessed by him, we are, we've fallen away and we're lost in the darkness.

12:31.287 --> 12:40.318
And so, you know, instead of being carried along by the Holy Spirit, we are now all by ourselves and we're lost.

12:41.419 --> 12:50.450
And so, in, when this coin was around the woman's neck, this coin would reflect the light and shine.

12:50.850 --> 12:53.114
But now in the dust, it had disappeared.

12:53.334 --> 12:53.935
It was lost.

12:54.737 --> 12:58.423
But this coin was still very valuable to the woman.

12:58.984 --> 13:03.031
So she lit an oil lamp, you know, to find it.

13:03.512 --> 13:06.878
And she swept the house and she kept seeking, not giving up.

13:07.719 --> 13:09.582
And that's how special we are to God.

13:10.384 --> 13:13.950
She determined in our heart, I'm going to do everything I can to find it.

13:14.832 --> 13:16.274
And she continued.

13:16.578 --> 13:17.920
till she found the coin.

13:18.440 --> 13:35.280
And this is a picture of the Holy Spirit who searches for each precious soul lost in the darkness, shining his light on us, revealing Jesus to us and sweeps away the dust and the doubts and the unbelief from us so that we can see the light.

13:35.720 --> 13:39.164
And when we can see the light, then we reflect it, you see.

13:39.745 --> 13:44.370
And when she found the coin, she lifted it up and rejoiced.

13:44.706 --> 13:47.269
And that's a picture of our salvation when we're found.

13:47.830 --> 13:58.244
We're taken out of the hands of the kingdom of darkness, and we're washed clean, praise God, and held secure in the hands of the Holy Spirit.

13:58.785 --> 14:05.714
And the Holy Spirit then raises us up and lifts our spirit up into heavenly places, no longer to be trodden underfoot.

14:06.335 --> 14:14.386
And then she called her friends and neighbors again saying, rejoice with me, let's have a party, for I found the peace that I had lost.

14:14.466 --> 14:20.453
So there is much joy in the presence of the angels over just one sinner that repents.

14:20.473 --> 14:22.075
That's how much God loves you.

14:22.095 --> 14:27.823
You are that one coin and you're so special that the Holy Spirit searches after you.

14:27.863 --> 14:34.611
All your life until he finds you and then he lifts you up.

14:34.631 --> 14:35.712
He washes you clean.

14:36.273 --> 14:40.979
He carries you and now you can shine the light.

14:41.700 --> 14:42.301
Praise God.

14:42.881 --> 14:43.442
And so

14:45.250 --> 14:46.712
That is the second parable.

14:47.012 --> 14:51.317
The third parable, which is the major parable, is the parable of the prodigal son.

14:51.357 --> 14:52.678
That's what it's usually called.

14:52.738 --> 14:56.603
But really, it's a story about the prodigal father.

14:56.623 --> 14:59.486
Now, the word prodigal means excessive, all right?

14:59.506 --> 15:05.112
So he's called the prodigal son because he was excessive in his sinful lifestyle.

15:05.813 --> 15:13.682
But it's also really about the prodigal father who is excessive in his love for us.

15:14.114 --> 15:19.742
We, in the story, we, of course, are the prodigal son that is lost in sin.

15:20.944 --> 15:23.107
And let's have a look at God's love.

15:23.167 --> 15:26.192
And of course, now this is a picture of the Father, the Father God.

15:27.454 --> 15:32.181
And it says that a certain man had two sons.

15:33.442 --> 15:35.045
This is verse 11.

15:36.166 --> 15:40.913
And the younger of them said to his Father, Father, give me the portion of goods that falls to me.

15:41.414 --> 15:44.018
Now this was a real insult, especially in those days.

15:44.738 --> 15:48.263
He insulted his father saying, I can't wait for you to die.

15:48.283 --> 15:50.265
I want my inheritance now.

15:50.926 --> 15:53.049
I want to leave home and do whatever I want.

15:53.069 --> 15:55.853
I want to live my own life.

15:56.694 --> 16:00.198
And that's again a picture of us in sin going our own way.

16:00.679 --> 16:02.641
We want to just please ourselves.

16:03.362 --> 16:08.309
And so the father amazingly divided to them his livelihood.

16:08.749 --> 16:12.274
So the older son actually would have got

16:12.770 --> 16:40.978
the double portion and this this younger son got his portion and the estate was divided and not many days after the younger son gathered all everything all his wealth together which is a third of the whole family wealth and he journeyed to a far country that's like us when we go away and sin we go far away from God our father and there he wasted his possessions with protocol or excessive living

16:41.474 --> 16:47.861
just indulged himself, blew all his money and spent it all on himself.

16:48.001 --> 16:49.122
What a picture of a sinner.

16:50.544 --> 16:51.725
No thought for his father.

16:52.666 --> 16:57.251
But when he had spent all there arose a severe famine in that land and he began to be in want.

16:57.932 --> 16:59.313
And that's of course what happens.

17:00.234 --> 17:07.902
Eventually sin fails to satisfy and it brings you to a place where you are in a desperately bad place.

17:08.803 --> 17:11.346
And he would have lost all his friends who were just

17:11.522 --> 17:39.090
once he lost his money he lost his friends and he was now suffering the consequences of sin because all sin brings a curse and a famine came and what happens when we go in sin we come into a spiritual famine and then an actual physical famine he had lost everything he was in rags wandering the streets as a beggar and he going lower and lower

17:39.426 --> 17:47.720
Verse 15, then he went and joined himself to a citizen of that country, and then he took a job that would be the worst job for a Jew, which was looking off the pigs.

17:48.862 --> 17:58.197
And he sent him into his fields to feed swine, and he would gladly fill his stomach with the pods that the swine ate so that no one gave him anything.

17:58.217 --> 18:02.284
So now he's in the pig pen of sin, the lowest place of all.

18:02.745 --> 18:05.970
He was so hungry that he was desperate to eat the food

18:06.210 --> 18:06.811
for the pigs.

18:06.891 --> 18:09.454
So the pigs had a higher status than he did.

18:10.396 --> 18:13.620
And he had now lost all self-respect.

18:13.720 --> 18:15.623
He had really hit bottom.

18:15.923 --> 18:23.493
And sometimes we have to hit the bottom before we'll come to our right mind and turn back to God.

18:24.334 --> 18:36.050
And so it says, when he came to his senses, when he came to himself, he realized now he was able to repent actually here.

18:36.130 --> 18:40.677
He came to himself and he said, how many of my father's hired servants?

18:41.098 --> 18:48.669
And these are the lowest servants, not paid all the time, but they're hired on a temporary basis when the need arises.

18:48.689 --> 18:54.558
So this is the lowest servant, but even they have bred enough and to spare and I perish.

18:54.778 --> 18:55.840
I'm dying with hunger.

18:56.681 --> 18:57.402
I will arise.

18:57.482 --> 18:58.444
Now he makes a choice.

18:59.045 --> 19:01.148
I am, this is repentance.

19:01.168 --> 19:02.610
I'm going to turn from my sin.

19:03.458 --> 19:05.802
This is no good.

19:06.403 --> 19:08.065
And I'm going to return to my Father.

19:08.085 --> 19:22.167
You see, when you go away from God, repent and return to God, I will rise and go to my Father and say to him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, against God in other words, and before you.

19:22.187 --> 19:25.512
And I am no longer worthy to be called your son.

19:25.592 --> 19:27.495
Make me like one of your hired servants.

19:28.096 --> 19:29.999
He would just take me back on any basis.

19:30.720 --> 19:31.762
Now we're going to see that

19:32.610 --> 19:33.931
the father's going to surprise him.

19:34.892 --> 19:37.195
But notice he acknowledges his sin.

19:37.255 --> 19:38.756
You have to acknowledge your sin.

19:39.136 --> 19:43.961
You have to return to God and you in the hope that he will receive you.

19:45.022 --> 19:47.525
And it says, and he arose and came to his father.

19:47.605 --> 19:52.330
And as he was walking home, he must have been thinking, will my father take me back?

19:53.050 --> 19:56.113
Or will he be angry and reject me as I deserve?

19:56.173 --> 20:00.818
And the Pharisees who had been listening to the story would have saying no way

20:01.090 --> 20:02.692
is this father going to take him back?

20:02.772 --> 20:07.198
He's going to deal with him, rebuke him and all the rest.

20:07.958 --> 20:13.325
He thinks he could come back even as a servant.

20:13.405 --> 20:14.767
That was crazy to them.

20:15.348 --> 20:16.709
But now is the big twist.

20:16.789 --> 20:17.911
Here's the big surprise.

20:18.291 --> 20:20.174
The Pharisees did not see this coming.

20:20.935 --> 20:28.324
It says in verse 20, that while he was still a great way off, his father saw him and had compassion and ran and fell on his neck and kissed him.

20:28.964 --> 20:30.226
See, this is extraordinary.

20:30.850 --> 20:35.274
You see, the father had never turned his back on his beloved son, despite his sin.

20:36.015 --> 20:40.439
Every day he woke up saying, my boy, maybe he'll come back home today.

20:40.840 --> 20:45.584
So often he was looking on the horizon to see maybe he's coming back.

20:46.205 --> 20:49.648
Every time he saw someone out in the distance, he'd say, is that my son?

20:50.589 --> 20:58.497
Day after day, week after week, month after month, year, even years, but he didn't go up home because he loved his son so much.

20:58.837 --> 20:59.858
And then one day,

21:00.098 --> 21:02.601
He saw a figure in the distance, a bit disheveled.

21:04.803 --> 21:05.624
Could that be my son?

21:05.684 --> 21:06.705
It looks a bit like him.

21:08.047 --> 21:10.590
And he looked again and as he got closer he arrived.

21:10.970 --> 21:12.312
Yes, that's my son.

21:13.153 --> 21:20.341
And with tears of joy, his heart full of love caused him in a very undignified way to actually run.

21:20.381 --> 21:25.106
Now, the Pharisees would think he'd stand there waiting for the son.

21:25.570 --> 21:29.174
You know, let's see what excuses you can come up with, crossing his arms.

21:29.234 --> 21:38.723
No, the Father just forgets himself and he runs and he runs and he runs to his son because when you start coming back to God, God will run back to you.

21:40.685 --> 21:52.596
And as he got close, he would smell the horrible smell of pigs all over him and we are covered with the horrible stench of our sin and yet that doesn't, didn't stop his love.

21:52.877 --> 21:54.258
In fact, he even

21:54.882 --> 21:57.246
embraced him, embraced his son.

21:57.927 --> 22:09.905
And so his love was stronger than the repugnance of that stench, which is our sin is a stench in God's nostril, but he still loves us and receives us when we come back to him.

22:10.445 --> 22:13.790
And he kept kissing him and hugging him and so on.

22:13.831 --> 22:22.484
And the son said to him, the words he had planned, father, I've sinned against heaven and in your sight and I'm no longer to be worthy to be called your son.

22:22.544 --> 22:24.146
And

22:24.354 --> 22:26.117
That's all the father needed to hear.

22:26.157 --> 22:28.581
And he immediately forgave him.

22:28.601 --> 22:37.355
And then it says, he says, the father said to his servants, hurry, bring the best robe and put it on him.

22:38.076 --> 22:45.989
In other words, he doesn't want him to come back in shame for everyone to point the finger at his son, covered in rags.

22:46.370 --> 22:49.335
He said, give him our best robe, clothe him.

22:49.375 --> 22:51.218
And that's what happens.

22:51.586 --> 22:53.788
when make him look like me in other words.

22:53.848 --> 23:00.795
And the Bible says that the Isaiah 61 10 says, he has clothed me with the garments of salvation.

23:01.075 --> 23:04.678
We are clothed with the righteousness of Christ when we come to him.

23:04.718 --> 23:06.320
We are clothed in his righteousness.

23:06.700 --> 23:08.902
We are clothed as his son.

23:08.962 --> 23:12.506
He's accepted him, not as a servant, but as a son.

23:12.546 --> 23:20.273
And so the whole, the community will see his son has returned and the Father has accepted him.

23:20.854 --> 23:21.394
And so

23:21.986 --> 23:26.713
Only the father saw his true state, but everyone could see him clothed.

23:27.053 --> 23:30.218
He gives him a brand new start, in other words, he forgives him.

23:30.638 --> 23:34.224
And it says he put a ring on his hand and put sandals on his feet.

23:35.005 --> 23:42.155
And again, he had the dignity of having sandals now to walk as a son on the property.

23:42.195 --> 23:49.746
And the ring actually represents that he is now trusted by the father to represent him, because the ring would be used

23:49.858 --> 23:56.305
you know like a credit card or something like that as that he could represent the father in business.

23:56.807 --> 24:00.562
And then I'm sure he was also given a bath and we are washed.

24:00.994 --> 24:05.601
by the washing of regeneration and renewing of the Holy Spirit.

24:05.941 --> 24:11.650
And then he had a party, as in the other parables, verse 23, and bring the fatted calf.

24:11.690 --> 24:14.474
This is the calf that's been prepared for special occasions.

24:15.536 --> 24:18.080
Bring it here and kill it and let us eat and be merry.

24:18.120 --> 24:20.563
For this my son was dead and is alive again.

24:20.884 --> 24:23.608
He was lost and is found and they began to make merry.

24:24.129 --> 24:25.010
And he was so

24:25.090 --> 24:27.033
Happy, this is how much he loved his son.

24:27.093 --> 24:33.082
He forgot everything he did and just welcomed him with a party because he was dead, but now he's alive.

24:33.143 --> 24:36.949
You can tell the father's excitement.

24:37.309 --> 24:38.591
That's how much God loves you.

24:38.611 --> 24:41.375
That's how much he will receive you if you've turned away from him.

24:42.637 --> 24:43.619
Don't hide from God.

24:44.160 --> 24:48.146
Come back to him and he will rejoice that you've returned to him.

24:48.546 --> 24:52.671
And then, of course, the older son who represents the Pharisees was not pleased.

24:53.231 --> 24:57.336
We read that from verse 25, that the older son was kind of sulking.

24:57.396 --> 24:58.618
He was working in the field.

24:59.319 --> 25:01.341
And he didn't join the party.

25:01.862 --> 25:03.463
This was like the Pharisees.

25:03.704 --> 25:04.945
How dare he?

25:05.065 --> 25:05.846
The sinner.

25:06.627 --> 25:07.728
How dare he come back?

25:08.229 --> 25:12.554
And now the father has killed the fatted calf for him.

25:13.055 --> 25:15.858
And he was angry, it says, and he wouldn't go in.

25:15.938 --> 25:19.423
But the father loved this self-righteous son as well.

25:20.084 --> 25:24.129
He said, the father came out and pleaded with him in verse 28.

25:24.209 --> 25:28.195
And he answered and said to the father, look, I've served you all these years.

25:28.315 --> 25:35.404
I never broke any of your commandments, but you never gave me a young goat that I might marry with my friends.

25:37.547 --> 25:42.674
And but as soon as this, this other one came, he, he's devoured.

25:44.354 --> 25:48.038
your livelihood with harlots, and you killed the fatted car for him.

25:48.559 --> 25:50.602
And so he was just jealous, he was upset.

25:51.302 --> 26:06.801
And the father says to him, he's trying to win this son over, because this son does not have, although he's worked hard for his father, he's done it on a kind of rules basis, but he's not out of a real love.

26:07.782 --> 26:12.808
And, you know, he doesn't have the heart of his father.

26:12.868 --> 26:14.290
He doesn't know his father.

26:14.530 --> 26:17.293
He doesn't have any love for his other son.

26:18.094 --> 26:22.258
And so Jesus is exposing the lack of love of the Pharisees.

26:22.298 --> 26:27.544
And notice what the loving Father says in verse 31, Son, you're always with me.

26:28.144 --> 26:29.706
And all that I have is yours.

26:30.246 --> 26:36.493
Remember this other son didn't understand the grace of his father.

26:36.753 --> 26:40.177
His father had already given him his full inheritance.

26:40.197 --> 26:41.458
He owned everything.

26:42.338 --> 26:43.779
You see, all I have is yours.

26:44.220 --> 26:45.982
He could have had a party at any time.

26:46.582 --> 26:56.352
And yet he was operating with a slave mentality towards his father, rather than realizing he was the son of his beloved father.

26:57.012 --> 26:58.394
And all things were his.

26:59.094 --> 27:01.857
And so he didn't have a revelation of his father's love.

27:02.558 --> 27:06.361
And so he had no love in his heart for his brother.

27:07.122 --> 27:11.186
And so the father is trying to say, it was right that we should make merry.

27:11.330 --> 27:15.977
and be glad for your brother was dead and there's a life again and was lost and is found.

27:16.478 --> 27:19.723
And so when anyone comes to the Lord, we shouldn't rejoice.

27:20.144 --> 27:25.312
Whatever they've done in their past, you know, because that is what God is like.

27:25.372 --> 27:27.034
That's what Jesus is teaching here.

27:27.074 --> 27:30.740
God is like that towards every human being.

27:31.141 --> 27:31.742
He loves them.

27:31.762 --> 27:36.068
Yes, he knows the stench of our sin, but he loves us so much.

27:36.208 --> 27:39.794
And when anyone comes back to him and repents,

27:40.162 --> 27:46.830
He runs to them and welcomes them and throws a party in heaven on their behalf, praise God.

27:46.890 --> 27:48.012
That's what God is like.

27:48.072 --> 27:55.741
He's not like the Pharisees who are maybe outwardly very righteous and keep all the rules and yet have no love in their heart.

27:55.761 --> 27:57.323
That's not what we're to be like.

27:57.864 --> 28:00.146
We are to be like our heavenly Father.

28:00.186 --> 28:06.874
And so God is like the big-hearted Father, full of love and forgiveness.

28:07.475 --> 28:09.778
And He is like the good shepherd,

28:10.050 --> 28:15.579
who was willing to lay down his life for the sheep, to carry the sheep home.

28:15.920 --> 28:25.535
And he is like that woman who searched and saved her lost coin and then rejoiced.

28:25.555 --> 28:27.699
That's how much God loves you.

28:27.719 --> 28:28.781
So be encouraged by that.

28:28.961 --> 28:29.682
God bless you.

